				<div class="postbody">
				<a href="http://story.news.yahoo.com/news?tmpl=story&u=/nm/20040203/tv_nm/television_tivo_dc_3" target="_blank">http://story.news.yahoo.com/news?tmpl=story&u=/nm/20040203/tv_nm/television_tivo_dc_3</a>
<br />

<br />
I knew that TiVo had a thing about taking note of people's viewing habits, but the impression I got was more like the nielsens...ie: what channel you watch, and when.
<br />

<br />
I didn't know they could identify every solitary second of what you are doing. I don't own a TiVo (or any other kind of DVR), is it common knowledge that they can snoop your viewing habits to this high of a degree?
<br />

<br />
Anyone else find it more than a bit creepy?<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
