			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				I know they take statistics, was part of the reason my fiancée didn't want one in the house... I figure it is a way to be a Neilson family without the paperwork. They see what programs I watch. They see what commercials I forward thru and which I let play. 
<br />

<br />
Eventually they will realize that there are certain segments of the population (large ones I bet) that turn off every sport or religious program/commercial that is aired. Stop filling my Star Trek with save the christian children commercials or sports ads, I will only forward thru them. Don't advertise on the evening news sport section as I always flip channels at that time. 
<br />

<br />
Some statistics I don't mind them recording. I can still enjoy unrecorded programming in another room if I am concerned about big brother. A $10 switch makes it easy to redirect the signal. 
<br />

<br />
But if my viewing habits can help my favorite programs survive the ratings axe, please do keep tabs on me.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
