			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Your cable modem and any tivo-like device has a direct connection to the cable network. The cable company can connect to them via the co-ax connection and do whatever it is they do to monitor you and download stats. Tivo requires a dial-up connection to get program guide updates and probably sends that data to them via the phone line during that call.
<br />

<br />
You can always roll your own: <a href="http://www.mythtv.org" target="_blank">http://www.mythtv.org</a><br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
		</table>
		</td>
