				<div class="postbody">
				I'm more paranoid than most about privacy and monitoring, and I couldn't give one rat's %@$# about Tivo's reporting.
<br />

<br />
1) I love the device.  <img src="images/smiles/blush.gif" alt="blush" border="0" /> 
<br />
2) Reporting is anonymous and not tied to anything which could identify the end user -- I believe it's restricted to geographic location, and some level of age-data, however tivo and directv don't have age data on me (from me, anyway, it's on my credit report if they really wanted it).
<br />

<br />
If the reporting helps them be aware that we record every broadcast version of shows we REALLY like, that we turned off this_months_spingerfest_realityshow 3 minutes in, that we don't mind this commercial, but fast forward thru that one every time, then alls the better.
<br />

<br />
I don't have to fill out any retarded paperwork, I don't have to think about being a 'nielson family', and I, hopefully, will gradually see improvements to broadcasting.  As a plus for me, PVR's are (currently) likely to have a higher saturation level among geeks and the middle-to-upper classes, skewing the data away from "Today on Sally Jesse: My mother just told me she's a MAN!"...<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
