			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Actually, TV is getting ready to take a turn for the worse. (Yes, it CAN get worse than it is now!)
<br />

<br />
Ad revenue is falling due to PVRs allowing people to time shift and skip commercials. They will begin with the 1950s style product placement again (actually they already have if you look closely) but they will also start doing something worse: pop overs. Yes, on the TV. Watch comedy central if you want to see it in action... you can't go 10 minutes without a popup in the corner for the John Henson project.
<br />

<br />
TV is going to gravitate into two varieties: Pay for ad-free channels and pay-less spam channels. I'll continue to do what I've always done... leave the cable box off and rent the good shows from netflix on DVD, or buy them if they are good enough. No harm in ripping them from usenet either, they are much more prevalent than pirated movies right now.
<br />

<br />
I hope it dies a quick death. TV is such sub-par entertainment anyway. Nobody with a brain is going to miss it.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
